# Runtime report files — written by agent cron jobs; never commit/pull-overwrite these
# latest-*.md are pointer files updated every cron run; tracking them causes git pull
# to overwrite fresh agent output with stale committed content.
reports/cmo/latest-*.md
reports/cmo/*-202*.md
reports/bizdev/latest-*.md
reports/bizdev/*-202*.md
reports/cto/latest-*.md
reports/cto/*-202*.md
reports/cto/ceo-feedback/202*.json
reports/cto/ceo-feedback/202*.txt
reports/cto-briefings/*-202*.md
reports/ceo/latest-*.md
reports/ceo/*-202*.md
reports/ceo/review-state.json
reports/cfo/latest-*.md
reports/cfo/*-202*.md
# reports/daily/202*.md — TRACKED (post-run sync pushes these back; needed for local visibility)
reports/invoica-x-admin/logs/202*.md
reports/invoica-x-admin/drafts/

# Runtime state files — written by heartbeat-daemon, overwritten by git-pull if tracked
health.json
tier.json

# Memory files — generated by memory-agent, NOT tracked by git (git pull would restore stubs)
memory/daily-continuity.md
memory/long-term-memory.md
memory/daily-log-*.md
Arb-bot-main/wallet/
